         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Botanic Garden ¶ Melbourne, 28th June 1871 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ Allow me to ask whether you have any means of obliging me by ascertaining the approximate quantity of wood, sold for fuel, in your township. It oc...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.06.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Borough of Castlemaine</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Unit 50, VPRS 575 Borough of Castlemaine sundry records, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter written by G. Luehmann and signed by M.</p>
               </note>Botanic Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne, 28th June 1871</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me to ask whether you have any means of obliging me by ascertaining the approximate quantity of wood, sold for fuel, in your township. It occurs to me, that probably you have some wood market where information may be obtained; also perhaps that tolls exist, where some sort of record is kept of the number of woodcarts passing. I am anxious to learn the approximate quantity used in 1870, to append statistic notes on fuel supply to a public document which I am about to issue.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">B71.13.03, pp. 24-5.</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #0000ff; "> </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">Castlemaine is reported to have used 37,500 tons for fuel.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With obedience</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller, M.D.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
